SIMPLE: closeness
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Closeness
<hw>Close"ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The state of being
close.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Half stifled by the <qex>closeness</qex> of the room.</q>
<rj><qau>Swift.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We rise not against the piercing judgment of Augustus, nor the
extreme caution or <qex>closeness</qex> of Tiberius.</q>
<rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>An affectation of <qex>closeness</qex> and covetousness.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Narrowness; oppressiveness; strictness; secrecy;
compactness; conciseness; nearness; intimacy; tightness; stinginess;
literalness.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>close-packed</ent>⟦br⟧
